==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: State socialism
<hw>State socialism</hw>. <def>A form of socialism, esp. advocated in
Germany, which, while retaining the right of private property and the
institution of the family and other features of the present form of the
state, would intervene by various measures intended to give or maintain
equality of opportunity, as compulsory state insurance, old-age
pensions, etc., answering closely to socialism of the chair.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stateswoman</ent>⟦br⟧
